Detailed Description

template<class T>
class Sylph::Iterator< T >

Iterator provides a transparant interface for iterating over collections.

Each Iterable should have a specific implementation of this class. It is not required to implement all methods of this class.

A const Iterator should allow const access to items in the collection, but must not allow modification of those items. A non-const Iterator should allow both access and modification of the items. In order to comply to this behavior, it may be necessary to declare one or more fields as mutable.

This class is used implicitly by sforeach(), and therefore an implementation of this class is required for each Iterable that needs to be able to being iterated over by sforeach() .

Constructor & Destructor Documentation

template<class T>
Sylph::Iterator< T >::Iterator ( const Iterable< T > &  it  )  [inline]

Creates a new Iterator from an Iterable.

An Iterator can either be constructed explicitly with this constructor, in which case the correct type of Iterator for the particular collection needs to be known, or through Iterable::iterator() or Iterable::mutableIterator() .

The default implementation does nothing.

Parameters:
it The iterable to iterate over.

Member Function Documentation

template<class T>
virtual void Sylph::Iterator< T >::back (  )  const [virtual]

Moves the Iterator to the place "after" the last item, that is, it gives the pointer in the iterator such a value that hasNext returns false.

This method is useful for backward iterating, i.e. 

Iterator it = coll.getIterator(); // normal 'forward' iterator
 it.back(); // ready for backward iteration
Note:
You are not required to override this method if this Iterator cannot iterate forward

template<class T>
virtual void Sylph::Iterator< T >::front (  )  const [virtual]

Moves the Iterator to the place "before" the first item, that is, it gives the pointer in the iterator such a value that hasPrevious returns false.

Note:
You are not required to override this method if this Iterator cannot iterate backward.
